manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Future-Proof your System 80 Plus Titanium Certified Dark Power Pro 13 1600W is certified with 80 PLUS Titanium and a money-saving energy efficiency rating of up to 94.5%. This provides lots of benefits for high-end systems, including less power consumption and an overall cooler and quieter operation. The standby drain is below 0.1 watts. Future Proof Your System Dark Power Pro 13 1600W is an ATX 3.0 PSU and comes with both native integration of the two 12VHPWR connectors for next-generation PCIe 5.0 graphics cards, and 6 PCIe 6+2-pin connectors for support of current-gen GPUs. This makes the PSU extremely versatile and the perfect choice for present high-end systems and the ones to come. The New Standard of Power Dark Power Pro 13 offers 1600W of continuous power with 6 independent 12V rails. Even if the graphics card demands excessive power for a short time: Dark Power Pro 13 1600W handles power excursions up to double its rated power with ease. This ensures reliable operation with the next generation of processors and graphics cards.

Innovative Cooling Concept State-of-the-Art Digital Technology Experience the most technologically advanced power supply be quiet! has ever built! Using an advanced digital full bridge LLC technology results in higher efficiency, better regulation and lower ripple noise for an incomparably stable operation Frameless Silent Wings Fan The improved tripod-mounted be quiet! Silent Wings fan enables maximum airflow and a virtually inaudible operation. This is thanks to its unique, airflow-optimized fan blade design along with an advanced fluid-dynamic bearing. A 6-pole fan motor ultimately makes for less vibration, super-long life and minimal power consumption. Innovative Cooling Concept The split fan inlet of the Dark Power Pro 13 1600W is a specially shaped funnel that increases airflow while reducing unwanted turbulence. The wire-free design inside allows the cool air to reach all components flawlessly which ultimately leads to a longer lifespan.

Pushing the Performance Ready for Extreme Overclocking Dark Power Pro 13 1600W is particularly suitable for liquid nitrogen or helium overclocking, thanks to its state-of-the-art digital regulation. The overclocking key empowers you to manually switch between the default six 12V-rail mode and the alternative massive single-rail operation. Japanese 105°Capacitors Only the best components are used in Dark Power Pro 13 1600W. That is why this PSU features exclusively high-quality Japanese capacitors. They are rated at 105°C for stability, reliability, and a long operating life. Highest Convenience Individually sleeved cables of up to 120cm and cable combs simplify component installation and reduce annoying clutter. This results in increased airflow and improved cooling – even in the largest PC cases.

No compromises Magnificent Appearance Dark Power Pro 13 1300W not only captivates with its inner values. An extraordinary aluminum case and individually sleeved cables emphasize the highest standards of Dark Power Pro 13 1300W also on the outside.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Want a Rolls Royce?
reviews.reviewText: Bottom Line - this is the Rolls Royce of Computer Power Supply's. 1600 Watts of pure, efficient, clean power. No, I am not an employee of be quiet!, nor do I know anyone who works there. This is just the most efficient, best-made power supply - period. We build custom computers and used them almost exclusively in the 83 units we built in 2023. And when the budget allows only the Dark Power Pro 13 versions. You should spend a few extra dollars - you will never regret doing it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Power supply died after 30 minutes of use
reviews.reviewText: I built a new computer and have installed everything correctly. All connections are working. I installed Windows 11 and started listening to music while I worked on reinstalling my main programs. All of a sudden after roughly 30 minutes of use, everything shut off in an instant as though the computer was unplugged from the wall. I tried turning it back on, but nothing started up. There was also a static clicking sound coming from within the power supply which told me something was wrong with the power supply. My motherboard was getting some power, but only enough to light up all the lights including my ram sticks, but nothing started up. Also the unit has very sharp edges and I had to handle it carefully so as to not cut myself. I expected more out of Be Quiet!, a German brand with seemingly high quality products, but alas was disappointed.
